cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "steer-push: a pre-life test for a steer-vs-push (selection-vs-causation) criterion"
abstract: >-
  Toy dynamical-systems battery testing whether a criterion can separate when a
  physical difference STEERS a system (selection) from when it merely PUSHES it
  (causation), below life, against a fixed adversarial bar (FEP-flat and
  Deacon-PUSH). Includes an append-only pre-registration with predicted verdicts
  locked before each run.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: James
    given-names: Benjamin
version: 0.2.0
date-released: "2026-06-27"
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/benjaminjamesgit/steer-push"
keywords:
  - dynamical systems
  - selection versus causation
  - free energy principle
  - teleodynamics
  - pre-registration
